02:41.745 --> 02:43.831
I'll only be gone

02:41.745 --> 02:43.831
a couple hours, okay?

02:43.872 --> 02:46.125
You mean like the couple

02:43.872 --> 02:46.125
of hours you were jammed

02:46.166 --> 02:49.210
half-in and half-out of me

02:46.166 --> 02:49.210
when you were being born?

02:49.252 --> 02:51.296
Half an hour?

02:49.252 --> 02:51.296
I just don't understand

02:51.338 --> 02:53.799
what is so horrible

02:51.338 --> 02:53.799
about our family.

02:53.841 --> 02:55.216
Yes, she does.

02:55.258 --> 02:57.385
I mean, why on earth

02:55.258 --> 02:57.385
would you prefer

02:57.427 --> 02:58.846
to be somewhere else

02:58.887 --> 03:00.055
for Thanksgiving?

03:00.097 --> 03:01.389
I love her!

03:01.431 --> 03:04.101
And if the two of you

03:01.431 --> 03:04.101
are too dead inside

03:04.143 --> 03:07.146
to understand what that means,

03:04.143 --> 03:07.146
then I just pity you.

03:08.897 --> 03:13.234
(voice breaking):

03:08.897 --> 03:13.234
No, no, Dad, I understand.

03:13.276 --> 03:16.697
When you get a new toothbrush

03:13.276 --> 03:16.697
and you want to break it in...

03:22.285 --> 03:24.329
Go ahead and say it, Lois.

03:24.371 --> 03:27.875
Well, happy Thanksgiving.

03:27.916 --> 03:30.251
I'll just go over there

03:27.916 --> 03:30.251
and tell them I'm not coming.

03:30.293 --> 03:31.252
Do whatever you want.

03:31.294 --> 03:32.838
Even though your

03:31.294 --> 03:32.838
brother has

03:32.880 --> 03:35.132
traveled hundreds

03:32.880 --> 03:35.132
of miles with her.

03:35.174 --> 03:37.258
Piama.

03:35.174 --> 03:37.258
I know her name.

03:37.300 --> 03:38.844
Your family is going to be here,

03:38.886 --> 03:41.262
and we are going

03:38.886 --> 03:41.262
to have a lovely Thanksgiving.

03:41.304 --> 03:43.057
FRANCIS:

03:41.304 --> 03:43.057
I will not keep

03:41.304 --> 03:43.057
my voice down!

03:43.098 --> 03:44.683
What, you think they won't know

03:43.098 --> 03:44.683
in, like, five minutes

03:44.725 --> 03:46.267
that we're getting a divorce?!

03:46.309 --> 03:48.269
Sorry, we're having

03:46.309 --> 03:48.269
some problems.

03:48.311 --> 03:49.437
Having some problems?

03:49.479 --> 03:51.272
Is that what you

03:49.479 --> 03:51.272
call finding out

03:51.314 --> 03:53.859
that all the love that

03:51.314 --> 03:53.859
we shared was a lie?!

03:53.901 --> 03:55.110
Hi, Mom.

03:57.362 --> 04:00.281
Malcolm, you better go

03:57.362 --> 04:00.281
get your father.

04:00.323 --> 04:02.283
Malcolm!

04:03.410 --> 04:04.870
This party's pretty cool.

04:04.912 --> 04:06.163
And, you know,

04:06.205 --> 04:07.497
I think I've figured

04:06.205 --> 04:07.497
Kirsten out.

04:07.539 --> 04:10.209
It's more of a friend-brother

04:07.539 --> 04:10.209
kind of thing.

04:10.250 --> 04:12.753
It's not really sexual.

04:15.255 --> 04:16.297
Then again...

04:16.339 --> 04:17.716
Beer man.

04:17.758 --> 04:20.510
My stepdad drinks so much,

04:17.758 --> 04:20.510
he never counts it.

04:21.178 --> 04:22.179
Malcolm?

04:22.221 --> 04:23.304
Yeah, sure.

04:23.346 --> 04:26.307
Yeah, sure.

04:28.518 --> 04:30.979
Hey, guys, how's it going?

04:31.021 --> 04:33.899
I need something to warm up

04:31.021 --> 04:33.899
that Arctic wind

04:33.941 --> 04:35.358
she's blowing up there.

04:35.400 --> 04:37.236
No offense to your mother.

04:37.277 --> 04:38.319
I love her very much.

04:38.361 --> 04:40.114
It's cool, Art.

04:40.155 --> 04:41.364
All right. You kids have fun.

04:44.243 --> 04:45.326
Somebody drop a beer?

04:45.368 --> 04:46.327
(laughter)

04:46.369 --> 04:47.328
Sorry.

04:47.370 --> 04:48.496
My parents are

04:47.370 --> 04:48.496
a little less casual

04:48.538 --> 04:49.957
about the whole beer thing.

04:53.460 --> 04:55.921
I bet you kiss

04:53.460 --> 04:55.921
like a nine-year-old.

04:55.963 --> 04:57.798
What?

04:57.839 --> 04:59.133
What?

04:59.174 --> 05:01.342
Okay, this one I do know

04:59.174 --> 05:01.342
what she was doing.

05:01.384 --> 05:02.928
It was a total come-on.

05:02.970 --> 05:05.180
I'll show her

05:02.970 --> 05:05.180
how a nine-year-old can kiss.

05:08.642 --> 05:10.351
Hey.

05:20.028 --> 05:21.404
FRANCIS:

05:20.028 --> 05:21.404
Don't tell me not to cry!

05:21.446 --> 05:23.282
Maybe my tears

05:21.446 --> 05:23.282
will make an ocean

05:23.323 --> 05:25.366
and you can sail off

05:23.323 --> 05:25.366
on a boat

05:25.408 --> 05:27.286
to a new life without me!

05:27.327 --> 05:29.370
How did this happen?

05:27.327 --> 05:29.370
It's terrible.

05:30.289 --> 05:31.832
What's that look, Hal?

05:31.873 --> 05:33.458
Come on, Lois.

05:31.873 --> 05:33.458
You've been trying

05:33.500 --> 05:35.669
to undercut this relationship

05:33.500 --> 05:35.669
from the start.

05:35.710 --> 05:37.587
And now all of a sudden,

05:35.710 --> 05:37.587
they're getting a divorce

05:37.629 --> 05:39.173
and you had nothing

05:37.629 --> 05:39.173
to do with it?

05:39.214 --> 05:41.842
Please. You really think

05:39.214 --> 05:41.842
I have that much power

05:41.883 --> 05:44.385
to orchestrate people's lives

05:41.883 --> 05:44.385
besides yours?

05:44.427 --> 05:46.305
All I know is that

05:44.427 --> 05:46.305
our son is talking

05:46.345 --> 05:47.388
about ending his marriage--

05:47.430 --> 05:48.974
a marriage which

05:47.430 --> 05:48.974
you never supported.

05:49.016 --> 05:50.976
Hal, that's ridiculous.

05:49.016 --> 05:50.976
Fine, fine.

05:51.018 --> 05:52.894
You want me to go

05:51.018 --> 05:52.894
talk to Francis?

05:52.936 --> 05:54.395
Yes. No!

05:54.437 --> 05:56.982
No, no, no, no, no, no.

05:57.024 --> 06:00.027
This is some way for you

05:57.024 --> 06:00.027
to try to work out your agenda.

06:00.068 --> 06:02.321
Fine. I will not say

06:00.068 --> 06:02.321
a word to either one of 'em.

06:02.361 --> 06:03.404
Good.

06:03.446 --> 06:06.407
Wait.

06:03.446 --> 06:06.407
You won't say anything,

06:06.449 --> 06:08.327
which means you're just

06:06.449 --> 06:08.327
going to let

06:08.367 --> 06:09.703
this whole thing

06:08.367 --> 06:09.703
fall apart.

06:09.744 --> 06:11.579
Oh, I see your game, Lois.

06:11.621 --> 06:13.581
Hal, what is it

06:11.621 --> 06:13.581
you want me to do?

06:13.623 --> 06:15.209
No, no, you are not dragging me

06:15.250 --> 06:17.418
into your little Machiavellian

06:15.250 --> 06:17.418
schemes, thank you very much.

06:17.460 --> 06:21.256
No, you spun these

06:17.460 --> 06:21.256
tangled webs yourself, Lois.

06:21.298 --> 06:23.633
You get yourself out.

06:24.467 --> 06:26.053
See?

06:26.094 --> 06:27.637
The real balsamic

06:26.094 --> 06:27.637
has a smoother mouth feel.

06:27.679 --> 06:29.430
Good, you're back.

06:29.472 --> 06:31.225
I'm going to start prepping

06:29.472 --> 06:31.225
the herbs de Provence

06:31.266 --> 06:32.433
and sautéing the mushrooms.

06:32.475 --> 06:34.353
I need you to scrub these

06:32.475 --> 06:34.353
pots and pans again.

06:34.393 --> 06:35.312
What?

06:35.354 --> 06:37.314
No, I just finished those.

06:37.356 --> 06:38.815
Dad, look at this.

06:38.857 --> 06:41.442
The stubborn patina

06:38.857 --> 06:41.442
of tuna casserole,

06:41.484 --> 06:43.320
or enchilada loaf,

06:43.362 --> 06:44.863
or whatever in God's name

06:44.905 --> 06:47.490
this greasy spoon churns out

06:44.905 --> 06:47.490
night after soul-killing night.

06:47.532 --> 06:48.658
But not tonight.

06:48.700 --> 06:51.619
Tonight we go

06:48.700 --> 06:51.619
for greatness.

06:51.661 --> 06:52.913
Are you with me, Dad?

06:52.954 --> 06:53.747
No!

06:53.788 --> 06:55.540
This pot is clean enough, Reese.

06:55.582 --> 06:57.334
No one will taste this.

06:57.376 --> 06:58.877
All right, then.

06:58.919 --> 07:01.213
I guess no one will

06:58.919 --> 07:01.213
ever taste this!

07:05.424 --> 07:07.802
Oh, my God.

07:11.514 --> 07:13.308
Dewey, I need you to

07:11.514 --> 07:13.308
do something for me.

07:13.350 --> 07:14.351
No. No more.

07:14.393 --> 07:15.476
I'm sick of this.

07:15.518 --> 07:16.853
If I have to sculpt

07:15.518 --> 07:16.853
another radish

07:16.895 --> 07:18.355
or de-vein another prawn...

07:18.397 --> 07:20.481
Dewey, do you trust me?

07:20.523 --> 07:23.151
No.

07:20.523 --> 07:23.151
Do you fear me?

07:23.193 --> 07:24.652
No. Not in the long run.

07:24.694 --> 07:25.904
Come on, Dewey.

07:25.946 --> 07:27.655
It's just a couple

07:25.946 --> 07:27.655
of things I need

07:27.697 --> 07:29.532
that I couldn't get

07:27.697 --> 07:29.532
Dad to spring for.

07:29.574 --> 07:31.868
So here's $80 from

07:29.574 --> 07:31.868
Dad's wallet.

07:31.910 --> 07:34.495
The items on this

07:31.910 --> 07:34.495
list cost $240,

07:34.537 --> 07:36.664
so you'll have to

07:34.537 --> 07:36.664
turn on the cute.

07:36.706 --> 07:38.292
Can you handle it?

07:38.333 --> 07:40.127
I keep whatever's left over?

07:40.168 --> 07:41.169
Deal.

07:45.424 --> 07:46.507
Mom, can I talk to you?

07:46.549 --> 07:47.508
No, honey, please.

07:47.550 --> 07:49.177
Don't talk to me about this.

07:49.219 --> 07:50.887
No matter what I say,

07:49.219 --> 07:50.887
I'm going to be blamed.

07:50.929 --> 07:53.390
This is for you to work

07:50.929 --> 07:53.390
out with that woman.

07:53.432 --> 07:55.183
Piama.

07:53.432 --> 07:55.183
I know her name.

07:55.225 --> 07:56.726
Could you just listen

07:55.225 --> 07:56.726
to me for a second?

07:56.768 --> 08:00.688
If Piama and I ever were

07:56.768 --> 08:00.688
to get a divorce...

08:00.730 --> 08:02.316
Francis, don't even

08:00.730 --> 08:02.316
talk like that.

08:02.357 --> 08:03.358
I mean it.

08:03.400 --> 08:04.734
You really shouldn't.

08:07.279 --> 08:09.781
What were you going to say?

08:09.823 --> 08:13.534
If we ever were to split up,

08:09.823 --> 08:13.534
could I stay here for a while?

08:13.576 --> 08:16.955
God, Francis, I hate to

08:13.576 --> 08:16.955
even think of such a thing.

08:19.082 --> 08:22.752
But, yes, if such a terrible

08:19.082 --> 08:22.752
thing were to happen,

08:22.794 --> 08:24.921
of course, we'd

08:22.794 --> 08:24.921
be here for you.

08:24.963 --> 08:27.132
Thanks, Mom.

08:24.963 --> 08:27.132
I mean, it was

08:27.174 --> 08:29.550
a stupid fight, I guess,

08:27.174 --> 08:29.550
but it was emblematic

08:29.592 --> 08:31.761
of everything that was bad

08:29.592 --> 08:31.761
with the relationship.

08:31.803 --> 08:33.805
I mean, there are principles.

08:31.803 --> 08:33.805
Principles are important.

08:33.847 --> 08:36.557
I know. I mean, so what

08:33.847 --> 08:36.557
if I'd had a couple beers?

08:36.599 --> 08:41.562
How does it look in front of

08:36.599 --> 08:41.562
the guys if the woman's driving?

08:41.604 --> 08:42.814
What?

08:42.856 --> 08:44.565
She didn't care

08:42.856 --> 08:44.565
about my feelings at all.

08:44.607 --> 08:46.026
What?!

08:46.067 --> 08:47.568
What?

08:47.610 --> 08:49.737
Of all the idiotic,

08:47.610 --> 08:49.737
asinine things

08:49.779 --> 08:51.239
you have ever said, Francis,

08:51.281 --> 08:53.283
this has got to be

08:51.281 --> 08:53.283
one of the worst!

08:53.325 --> 08:54.368
I thought you were on my side.

08:54.409 --> 08:55.952
You don't have a side!

08:55.994 --> 08:58.372
Now, you are going to go and

08:55.994 --> 08:58.372
apologize to that woman.

08:58.413 --> 09:00.581
You are going to tell

08:58.413 --> 09:00.581
her that you are wrong

09:00.623 --> 09:02.250
and she is absolutely

09:00.623 --> 09:02.250
blameless.

09:02.292 --> 09:03.251
You really...?

09:02.292 --> 09:03.251
Go!

09:03.293 --> 09:04.878
Okay, okay.

09:07.797 --> 09:11.426
Yes, he is an idiot.

09:12.427 --> 09:14.388
Okay, Dad, get the bird.

09:14.429 --> 09:15.430
Here.

09:16.806 --> 09:18.683
What, this is

09:16.806 --> 09:18.683
the turkey you got?

09:18.725 --> 09:21.395
It's perfect.

09:18.725 --> 09:21.395
It's really small.

09:21.436 --> 09:22.770
Well, if it were

09:21.436 --> 09:22.770
any bigger,

09:22.812 --> 09:26.607
it wouldn't be able

09:22.812 --> 09:26.607
to fit inside of this!

09:28.651 --> 09:30.611
What? Y-You're going

09:28.651 --> 09:30.611
